    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>To style a block, you first need a way to target it in CSS. When you inspect a block's HTML, you will see that it has an ID selector. You can use that to target the block in CSS. But this is not the best way to style blocks in CSS. It can very quickly become hard to maintain. There is a better way - create predefined block styles.</p>
